  "title": "Sticky chicken - hard to translate (klewerige/taai hoender) - Marinda Kook",
  "description": null
 },
 "html": "<p>I was in the mood for lovely sticky, lick-your-fingers, syrupy chicken.  You'll need to wash your mouth and hands after eating this.  You can cut back on the sugar if you don't want something quite so sweet.<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-060.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1540\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 060\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-060-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></p>\n<p>INGREDIENTS:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 cup tomato sauce<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-009.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1530\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 009\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-009-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>1 cup brown sugar<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-001.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1528\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 001\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-001-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>1 cup honey<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-011.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1531\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 011\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-011-768x1024.jpg\" width=\"768\" height=\"1024\"></a></li>\n<li>1/2 cup soy sauce<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-013.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1532\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 013\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-013-768x1024.jpg\" width=\"768\" height=\"1024\"></a></li>\n<li>4 cloves of garlic<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-018.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1534\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 018\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-018-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>NOW:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>mix all the ingredients for the sauce together and cook for about 6 minutes on the stove<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-020.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1535\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 020\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-020-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>put the chicken and sauce in a mixing bowl and mix well<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-025.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1536\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 025\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-025-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>place it in an ovenproof dish and bake for 1 hour at 180 degrees Celsius<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-029.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1537\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 029\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-029-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>turn it over and over and over during the process<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-053.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1541\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 053\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-053-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>It shines. It's delicious. It asks for more.<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-043.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1543\" alt=\"MARINDA BLOG 043\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/MARINDA-BLOG-043-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></p>"
}
